{"title_page": "Wang Kai (actor)", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Wang (surname)|Wang]]}}\n{{infobox person\n| name = Wang Kai\n| image = 2017\u5e748\u670824\u65e5 \u4e0a\u6d77.jpg\n| alt = \n| caption = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1982|08|18}}\n| birth_place = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], China\n| nationality = Chinese | alma_mater = [[Central Academy of Drama]]\n| occupation = [[Actor]]\n| years_active = 2006\u2013present\n| module2 = {{infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| alias = Nick Wang\n | background = temporary\n| label = Deshe Film and Television Co., Ltd.\n}}\n}}\n{{Infobox Chinese\n|title='''Wang Kai'''\n|p=W\u00e1ng K\u01cei\n|t = {{linktext|\u738b|\u51f1}}\n|s = {{linktext|\u738b|\u51ef}}\n}}\n'''Wang Kai''' (born 18 August 1982) is a Chinese actor. He is known for his television roles in ''[[:zh:\u5317\u5e73\u65e0\u6218\u4e8b|All Quiet in Peking]]'' (2014), ''[[The Disguiser]]'' (2015), ''[[Nirvana in Fire]]'' (2015), ''[[Ode to Joy (TV series)|Ode to Joy]]'' (2016), ''[[When a Snail Falls in Love]]'' (2016), [[Stay with Me (TV series)|''Stay With Me'']] (2016), and ''[[Like a Flowing River]]'' (2018), as well as his film role in ''[[The Devotion of Suspect X (film)|The Devotion of Suspect X]]''.\n\nWang ranked 42nd on ''[[Forbes]]'' [[Forbes China Celebrity 100|China Celebrity 100]] list in 2017,<ref name=forbes>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/russellflannery/2017/09/22/actress-fan-bingbing-tops-new-forbes-china-celebrity-list/|title=Actress Fan Bingbing Tops New Forbes China Celebrity List|website=Forbes|date=September 22, 2017}}</ref> and 46th in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ent.sina.com.cn/s/m/2019-08-20/doc-ihytcitn0545378.shtml|title=\u798f\u5e03\u65af\u4e2d\u56fd\u53d1\u5e03100\u540d\u4eba\u699c \u5434\u4eac\u9ec4\u6e24\u80e1\u6b4c\u4f4d\u5217\u524d\u4e09|website=Sina|date=August 20, 2019|language=zh}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nWang was born in [[Wuhan]] in [[Hubei|Hubei Province]]. Although he wanted to become an actor after performing [[Thunderstorm (play)|''Thunderstorm'']] in school, his father wanted him to do sports while his mother wanted him to find a stable job.<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u5236\u670d\u5f1f\u5f1f \u738b\u51ef|url = http://epaper.oeeee.com/epaper/C/html/2014-11/02/content_3337296.htm?div=1|website =|accessdate = |date = November 2014|language=zh}}</ref> As a result, he worked as a book porter at [[Xinhua Bookstore]] after high school. During his free time, he took on side jobs such as attending activities organized by TV stations, taking model-training courses, and shooting commercials. \nIn 2002, during the shooting of a commercial, the director suggested Wang attend an acting academy. Wang resigned from his job and moved to Shanghai to take courses on acting at the [[Shanghai Theatre Academy]] in 2002. The next year, he applied for the [[Beijing Film Academy]] and the [[Central Academy of Drama]]. Wang received offers from both academies, and chose to attend the latter.<ref name=\"\u9c81\u8c6b\u6709\u7ea6\">{{cite video|url=http://v.ifeng.com/ent/zongyi/201601/0122c573-0b21-49ed-9bb4-48d16089650f.shtml |title= 20160119 \u9c81\u8c6b\u6709\u7ea6 \u738b\u51ef \u5ff5\u5ff5\u4e0d\u5fd8\u5fc5\u6709\u56de\u54cd |website=ifeng |date=January 19, 2016|language=zh}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Beginnings ===\nWhile a student at the Central Academy of Drama, Wang received his first acting role in ''Cold Autumn'' (2006), upon recommendation of his professor Zhang Xiaolong.<ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://www.tudou.com/programs/view/auUrFgl_MWw/\n| title = \u738b\u51ef\u505a\u5ba2\u97f3\u4e50\u6d3b\u529b\u6c47\n| date = August 30, 2013\n| website = [[Tudou]] \n| accessdate =2017-11-10 |language=zh\n}}</ref> In 2006, he participated in his first film ''My Puppy My Love'' (2012), an animal movie which focuses on dogs.<ref name=\"\u8d44\u6599\uff1a\u54cd\u5de2\u56fd\u9645\u827a\u4eba--\u738b\u51ef\">{{Cite web|title = \u8d44\u6599\uff1a\u54cd\u5de2\u56fd\u9645\u827a\u4eba--\u738b\u51ef |url = http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2011-06-09/15513329569.shtml|website = [[Sina Corp]]|accessdate =2017-11-10|language=zh|date = June 19, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/13/0106/12/8KHLO1DQ000300B1.html|title=\u300a\u6211\u7684\u72d7\u72d7\u6211\u7684\u7231\u300b\u70ed\u6620 \u738b\u51ef\u6f14\u6280\u53d7\u80af\u5b9a|date=January 6, 2013|website=Netease|language=zh}}</ref> \n \nIn 2007, Wang graduated from the Central Academy of Drama and signed with [[Huayi Brothers]]. During his first year with Huayi, he received no roles except for a minor role in ''Water Point Peach Blossom'' by Ma Lujian, the director of ''Cold Autumn''. He also had a minor role in the romantic comedy drama ''[[Calling For Love]]''. As the series would be aired in Taiwan, he learned to speak with a Taiwanese accent for the role.<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u738b\u51ef\u5077\u5e08\u8d3a\u519b\u7fd4 \u53f0\u6e7e\u8bdd\u51fa\u6f14\u300a\u547c\u53eb\u5927\u660e\u661f\u300b |url = http://yule.sohu.com/20100531/n272467834.shtml|website =[[Sohu]]|accessdate =2017-11-10|language=zh|date = May 31, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/10/0524/10/67ENRHJS00031GVS.html|title=\u738b\u51ef\u300a\u547c\u53eb\u5927\u660e\u661f\u300b\u6f14\u7ece\u7eaf\u7231\u6821\u56ed\u604b\u60c5|date=May 24, 2010|website=Netease|language=zh}}</ref>\n\n=== 2008\u201313: Rising popularity ===\nWang's first breakthrough in the industry was his casting in ''[[Yo soy Betty, la fea#Chou N\u00fc Wu Di|Ugly Wudi]]'', adapted from the American comedy series ''[[Ugly Betty]]''. The TV series was a commercial success, with the all four seasons being the highest viewed TV show in its time slot.<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u300a\u4e11\u5973\u65e0\u654c\u300b\u53d7\u5ba0\u6536\u89c6\u518d\u593a\u51a0 5\u65e5\u4e0a\u6f14\u5927\u7ed3\u5c40 |url = http://ent.163.com/10/0304/10/60U399OE00031GVS.html|website = [[NetEase]]|accessdate =2017-11-10|language=zh|date = March 4, 2010}}</ref> Although he tried out for the male lead, he was instead offered the role of Chen Jiaming, a sassy advertising director.<ref name=in>{{cite web|url=http://ent.ifeng.com/a/20151012/42506281_0.shtml|title=\u51ed\u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b\u8d70\u7ea2 \u738b\u51ef\uff1a\u60f3\u6311\u6218\"\u65af\u6587\u53d8\u6001\"|website=iFeng|language=zh|date=October 12, 2015}}</ref> Wang continued to play the role for all four seasons of the series\u2019 run between 2008 and 2010. While filming ''Ugly Wudi'', he left [[Huayi Brothers]] and signed with ''Ugly Wudi''\u2019s production company, Nesound International.<ref name=\"\u8d44\u6599\uff1a\u54cd\u5de2\u56fd\u9645\u827a\u4eba--\u738b\u51ef\"/>\n\nAfter the success of ''Ugly Wudi'', Wang found himself offered roles similar to his role in the series. Unwilling to be typecast, he rejected them all. Finally, he was offered the role of the a rugged and uneducated youth in ''[[:zh:\u77e5\u9752 (\u7535\u89c6\u5267)|Youth]]'' (2012).<ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2010-12-19/22083181610.shtml\n| title = \u603b\u5bfc\u6f14\u5f20\u65b0\u5efa\uff1a\u300a\u77e5\u9752\u300b\u6709\u4e00\u79cd\u60b2\u58ee\u7684\u7f8e\n| date = January 17, 2013\n| website = [[Sina Corp|Sina]]\n| accessdate = 2017-11-10|language=zh\n}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://ent.qq.com/a/20151011/025684.htm\n| title = \u738b\u51ef\uff1a\u6211\u73b0\u5728\u51c6\u5907\u597d\u4e86\n| date = October 12, 2015\n| website = [[Tencent]]\n| accessdate =2017-11-10 |language=zh\n}}</ref> He then starred in ''[[:zh:\u65b0\u795e\u63a2\u8054\u76df\u4e4b\u5305\u5927\u4eba\u6765\u4e86|New Detective Squad]]'' (2013), a Republican-era detective series loosely based on ''[[The Seven Heroes and Five Gallants|The Three Heroes and Five Gallants]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u300a\u65b0\u795e\u63a2\u806f\u76df\u300b\u767b\u592e\u516b \u738b\u51f1\u9ede\u71c3\u300e\u5075\u63a2\u71b1\u300f\u98a8\u6f6e|url=http://ent.big5.enorth.com.cn/system/2013/08/08/011208797.shtml|website=[[Sina Corp]]|accessdate=2017-11-10|language=zh|date=August 8, 2013}}</ref> The series had high viewership in mainland China and developed a small cult following online.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u300a\u65b0\u795e\u63a2\u8054\u76df\u300b\u767b\u9646\u592e\u89c6 \u5f20\u4fea\u5e05\u6c14\u903c\u4eba\u60ca\u8273\u767b\u573a|url=http://ent.163.com/13/0819/14/96LA187Q00032DGD.html|website=[[NetEase]]|accessdate=2017-11-10|language=zh|date=August 19, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\u5168\u5458B\u7ad9\u7206\u7ea2\u662f\u4e8c\u6b21\u5143\u9006\u88ad\uff1f|url=http://xw.qq.com/a/ENT/20151119047869/ENT2015111904786905|website=[[Tencent]]|accessdate=2017-11-10|language=zh|date=November 11, 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== 2014\u20132015: Breakthrough ===\nIn 2013, with the disbandment of Nesound\u2019s management department, Wang joined Shandong Television & Film. His first role under the company was a police officer in the critically acclaimed historical drama ''[[:zh:\u5317\u5e73\u65e0\u6218\u4e8b|All Quiet in Peking]]'', which was released in 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u300a\u5317\u5e73\u65e0\u6218\u4e8b\u300b\u738b\u51ef\u6f14\u6280\u7206\u53d1 \u62a2\u620f\u6551\u70e8\u5144|url = http://ent.163.com/14/1111/14/AAPC78AO00031GVS.html|website =[[NetEase]]|accessdate =2017-11-10 |language=zh|date=November 11, 2014}}</ref> This marked a turning point in his career. Wang was praised for his ability to hold his own against multiple acclaimed veteran actor.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u300a\u5317\u5e73\u65e0\u6218\u4e8b\u300b\u738b\u51ef\u5bf9\u9635\u8001\u620f\u9aa8\u6f14\u6280\u529f\u529b\u53d7\u80af\u5b9a|url=http://yule.sohu.com/20141011/n405008288.shtml|website=[[Sohu]]|date=October 11, 2014|accessdate=2017-11-10|language=zh}}</ref> The same year, he starred in the historical film, ''[[A Murder Beside Yanhe River]]'', where he plays a [[Chinese Workers' and Peasants' Red Army]] officer who becomes a murder suspect.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Revolutionary legal drama hits Chinese theaters|url = http://www.china.org.cn/arts/2014-12/04/content_34227673.htm|website =China.org.cn|accessdate =2017-11-10 |language=|date=December 4, 2014}}</ref> The film premiered in December 2014, and Wang received his first acting award, the Best New Actor Award at the 9th Chinese Youth Film Forum for his performance in the film.<ref name=best>{{Cite web|title = \u7b2c9\u5c4a\u534e\u8bed\u9752\u5e74\u5f71\u50cf\u8bba\u575b\u95ed\u5e55 \u97e9\u5bd2\u7b49\u83b7\u9881\u5e74\u5ea6\u65b0\u9510\u5f71\u4eba|url = http://ent.people.com.cn/n/2014/1106/c1012-25989188.html|website =[[People's Daily]]|accessdate =2017-11-10 |language=zh|date = November 6, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2014, when Hou Hongliang resigned from Shandong Film & Television to focus on Daylight Entertainment Ltd., Wang left with him for Daylight Entertainment.<ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://et.21cn.com/tv/roll/a/2015/1019/09/30165714.shtml\n| title = \u4faf\u9e3f\u4eae\u7684\u9020\u661f\u79d8\u8bc0\uff1a\u70ed\u8877\u7efc\u827a\u7684\u6f14\u5458\u6211\u4eec\u4e0d\u4f1a\u9009\u62e9\n| work = et.21.cn.com \n| date = October 19, 2015\n| accessdate =2017-11-10|language=zh \n}}</ref> He then starred in three television series produced by Daylight Entertainment: ''[[Nirvana in Fire]]'', ''[[The Disguiser]]'', and ''[[Love Me If You Dare (TV series)|Love Me If You Dare]]''. Wang played a loyal and capable triple agent in ''[[The Disguiser]]'', the neglected prince [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xiao Jingyan, Prince Jing|Xiao Jingyan]] who climbs his way to the throne with the help of his best friend in ''[[Nirvana in Fire]]'' and the protagonist's best friend in ''Love Me If You Dare''.<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b\u66dd\u5149\u9635\u5bb9 \u80e1\u6b4c\u738b\u51ef\u9ec4\u7ef4\u5fb7\u52a0\u76df|url = http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2013-12-10/10114057723.shtml?bsh_bid=322784179|website =[[Sina Corp]]|accessdate =2017-11-10|language=zh|date = December 10, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://ent.people.com.cn/n/2015/0919/c1012-27607354.html?t123\n| work = People.com\n| title = \u300a\u4f2a\u88c5\u8005\u300b\u70ed\u64ad \u9773\u4e1c\u738b\u51ef\u9093\u8d85\u6f14\u6280\"\u5bf9\u5f97\u8d77\u8fd9\u5f20\u8138\n| date = September 22, 2015\n| accessdate =2017-11-10 |language=zh \n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2015-11-11/doc-ifxkniur3059034.shtml|title=\u300a\u4ed6\u6765\u4e86\u300b\u738b\u51ef\u8be0\u91ca\u5e72\u63a2\u674e\u718f\u7136\u5236\u670d\u8bf1\u60d1|work=Sina|language=zh|date=November 11, 2015}}</ref> All three dramas were critical and commercial successes, and Wang received acclaim for his versatile acting.<ref>{{Cite web|title = War spy drama 'The Disguiser' dominates ratings|url = http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/942561.shtml|website=[[The Global Times]]|access-date =2017-11-10 |date = September 15, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Winning success with sincerity: \u2018Nirvana in Fire\u2019 restores confidence in period shows|url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/946888.shtml|website=[[The Global Times]]|accessdate=2017-11-10}}</ref><ref name=crime />\n\nFollowing the airing of these dramas, Wang experienced a sharp rise in popularity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/969783.shtml|title=Male Asian actors gaining a following abroad|date=February 22, 2016|work=[[The Global Times]]}}</ref><ref name=in /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ahtv.cn/c/2015/1010/00615473_3.html|title=\u4f2a\u88c5\u8005\u7405\u740a\u699c\u9738\u5c4f \u80e1\u6b4c\u9773\u4e1c\u738b\u51ef3\u4eba2\u90e8\u620f\u7206\u7ea2|website=Anhui TV|language=zh|date=October 10, 2015}}</ref> He was nominated for the Best Actor award at the [[Huading Awards]] and [[Shanghai Television Festival]] for his performance in ''The Disguiser'' and ''Nirvana in Fire'' respectively, and won the Best Supporting Actor award at the [[Asia Rainbow TV Awards]]. Wang had become a regular in both magazines and fashion events, and also received several endorsement deals.<ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://tech.qq.com/a/20160114/044903.htm\n| title = 360\u53d1\u5e03\u5947\u9177\u624b\u673a\u6781\u5ba2\u7248 \u6f14\u5458\u738b\u51ef\u62c5\u4efb\u4ee3\u8a00\u4eba\n| work = [[Tencent]]\n| date = January 14, 2016\n| accessdate =2017-11-10 |language=zh \n}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://weibo.com/3612234962/Dj9YYAgar\n| title = \u738b\u51ef\u4ee3\u8a00\u7231\u5938\n| date = February 23, 2016\n| accessdate =2017-11-10 |language=zh\n}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://weibo.com/3764535807/DjwprdDCI\n| title = \u5f88\u9ad8\u5174\u4e0e\u54c1\u724c\u643a\u624b\n| date = February 25, 2016\n| accessdate = |language=zh\n}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://weibo.com/3256651197/DmbMsfh5b\n| title = \u770b\u65b0\u95fb\u8fd8\u662f\u5f97\u7528\u641c\u72d0\n| date = March 14, 2016\n| accessdate = |language=zh\n}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://weibo.com/ttarticle/p/show?id=2309403953757548315604\n| title = \u79d1\u666e\u7bc7-\u5149\u660e\u690d\u7269\u6d3b\u529b\u4e73\u9178\u83cc\u996e\u54c1\n| date = March 16, 2016\n| accessdate =2017-11-10 |language=zh \n}}</ref>\n\n=== 2016\u2013present: Mainstream success ===\nIn 2016, he featured in metropolitan romance drama ''[[Ode to Joy (TV series)|Ode to Joy]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u300a\u6b22\u4e50\u9882\u300b\u66dd\u5b9a\u5986\u7167 \u6469\u767b\u9020\u578b\u6f14\u7ece\u90fd\u5e02\u65f6\u5c1a|url = http://ent.163.com/photoview/00B70003/571149.html#p=B3FSQH6900B70003|website = [[NetEase]]|accessdate =2017-11-10|language=zh|date=}}</ref> Although he did not appear until episode 11, Wang in association with the show was one of the most discussed topics on social medias.<ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://www.yan.sg/yingxiaozhan/\n| title = \u5927\u6570\u636e\u65f6\u4ee3\uff0c\u4e13\u5bb6\u5e2e\u4f60\u6252\u300a\u6b22\u4e50\u9882\u300b\u7684\u8425\u9500\u6218\n| date = May 15, 2016\n| accessdate =2017-11-10 |language=zh\n}}</ref> He reunited with his ''Ode to Joy'' co-star [[Wang Ziwen]] in crime thriller ''[[When a Snail Falls in Love]]'', adapted from Ding Mo's novel of the same name.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.zj.xinhuanet.com/yltd/2016-04/20/c_1118682932.htm|title=\u5982\u679c\u8717\u725b\u6709\u7231\u60c5\u5f00\u673a \u6f14\u5458\u9635\u5bb9\u63ed\u79d8|date=April 20, 2016|website=[[Xinhua News Agency]]|access-date=2017-11-10|language=zh}}</ref> The drama was a hit with local and overseas audience, and received 9.8 out 10 score on viki.com.<ref name=crime>{{cite web|url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1019807.shtml|title=Drawn to the suspenseful plots, diverse characters, and gripping storytelling techniques, foreign fans of Chinese crime dramas can be found all over the globe|date=November 24, 2016|work=[[The Global Times]]}}</ref> The same year, Wang starred alongside [[Joe Chen]] in romance drama ''[[Stay with Me (TV series)|Stay with Me]]''<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u300a\u653e\u5f03\u6211\u6293\u7d27\u6211\u300b\u5f00\u62cd \u9648\u4e54\u6069\u738b\u51ef\u9996\u5408\u4f5c|url = http://ent.163.com/15/1222/05/BBDRJCNK00032DGD.html|website = [[NetEase]]|accessdate =2017-11-10 |language=zh|date = December 22, 2015}}</ref> and in [[Jackie Chan]]'s action comedy film ''[[Railroad Tigers]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u7535\u5f71\u300a\u94c1\u9053\u98de\u864e\u300b\u9ec4\u5b50\u97ec\u738b\u51ef\u738b\u5927\u9646\u52a0\u76df|url = http://ent.sina.com.cn/m/c/2016-01-13/doc-ifxnkvtn9935247.shtml|website = Sina|access-date =2017-11-10|language=zh|date = January 13, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Wang starred in mystery-thriller  ''[[The Devotion of Suspect X (film)|The Devotion of Suspect X]]'', adapted from the [[The Devotion of Suspect X|Japanese novel of the same name]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.mtime.com/2017/03/06/1567023.html|title=\u300a\u5acc\u7591\u4ebax\u7684\u732e\u8eab\u300b\u63d0\u68633.31 \u738b\u51ef\u5f20\u9c81\u4e00\u6797\u5fc3\u5982\u63d0\u524d\u7834\u89e3\u4eba\u751f\u96be\u9898|date=March 6, 2018|website=Mtime|language=zh}}</ref> The film was a box office success.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.screendaily.com/news/china-box-office-ghost-in-the-shell-wins-weekend-but-kong-still-top/5116681.article|title= China box office: 'Ghost In The Shell' wins weekend but 'Kong' still top|accessdate=2017-11-10|work= [[Screen Daily]]|language= English|date=April 4, 2017}}</ref> The same year, he was announced to be playing [[Cao Cao]] in the upcoming film adaptation of popular RPG game ''[[Dynasty Warriors]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/m/c/2017-09-06/doc-ifykpysa3552268.shtml|title=\u300a\u771f\u4e09\u56fd\u65e0\u53cc\u300b\u62cd\u771f\u4eba\u7248 \u738b\u51ef\u626e\u66f9\u64cd\"\u7d2b\u6218\u888d\"\u66dd\u5149|date=September 6, 2017|work=Sina|language=zh}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Wang starred in ''[[A Better Tomorrow 2018]]'', directed by [[Ding Sheng (director)|Ding Sheng]] and a remake of the [[A Better Tomorrow|original classic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/m/c/2017-02-21/doc-ifyarrcf5165124.shtml|title=\u738b\u5927\u9646\u9a6c\u5929\u5b87\u62cd\u300a\u82f1\u96c4\u672c\u82724\u300b \u738b\u51ef\u677f\u5bf8\u9020\u578b\u66dd\u5149|work=Sina|language=zh|date=February 21, 2017}}</ref> He returned to the small screen with the period drama ''[[Like a Flowing River]]'', based on the novel ''Da Jiang Da He'' written by A Nai and set during Chinese economic reform in 1978.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2017-11-13/doc-ifynstfh6764008.shtml|title= \u300a\u5927\u6c5f\u5927\u6cb3\u300b\u516c\u5e03\u7537\u4e00\u53f7 \u738b\u51ef\u503e\u60c5\u6f14\u7ece\u65f6\u4ee3\u7f29\u5f71|date=November 13, 2017|website=Sina|language=zh}}</ref> The drama was a critical and commercial success, receiving positive reviews and topping ratings in its time slot.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://media.people.com.cn/n1/2018/1226/c40606-30487548.html|title=\u300a\u5927\u6c5f\u5927\u6cb3\u300b\u95ee\u9f0e\u5e74\u5ea6\u5267\u738b \u4e3a\u556580\u540e90\u540e\u4f1a\u8ffd\u7740\u770b|date=December 16, 2018|website=People's Daily|language=zh}}</ref> Wang received acclaim for a his portrayal of a talented young man who fought against all odds to eventually becomes a technical engineer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2018-12-17/doc-ihqhqcir7500644.shtml|title=\u300a\u5927\u6c5f\u5927\u6cb3\u300b\u6254\u6389\u5076\u50cf\u5305\u88b1 \u738b\u51ef\u53d8\u8eab\u201c\u571f\u5473\u5c11\u5e74\u201d|date=December 17, 2018|website=Sina|language=zh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.huanqiu.com/movie/yingshi-neidi/2018-12/13884998.html|title=\u300a\u5927\u6c5f\u5927\u6cb3\u300b\u738b\u51ef\u54ed\u620f\u4f20\u795e\u6f14\u6280\u5f81\u670d\u89c2\u4f17|date=December 24, 2018|website=Global Times|language=zh}}</ref> He was nominated for the [[Magnolia Award for Best Actor in a Television Series]].<ref name=ml />\n\nIn 2020, Wang starred in historical drama ''[[Held in the Lonely Castle]]'', portraying [[Emperor Renzong of Song]].<ref name=serenade>{{cite web|url=http://hn.people.com.cn/n2/2020/0403/c356341-33925935.html|title=\u300a\u6e05\u5e73\u4e50\u300b\u5b9a\u68634\u67086\u65e5 \u738b\u51ef\u6c5f\u758f\u5f71\u5c55\u73b0\u4ec1\u5b97\u76db\u6cbb|date=April 3, 2020|website=People's Daily|language=zh}}</ref>  The same year, he starred in the crime thriller drama ''Hunting'' as a police officer.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2019-06-10/doc-ihvhiews7860431.shtml|title=\u65b0\u5267\u300a\u730e\u72d0\u300b\u5b98\u5ba3\u4e3b\u6f14 \u738b\u51ef\u642d\u6863\u738b\u9e25\u4e0a\u6f14\u8de8\u56fd\u8ffd\u9003|date=June 10, 2019|website=Sina|language=zh}}</ref>\n\n==Other activities==\nIn February 2016, Wang co-founded Deshe Entertainment (Tianjin) Ltd. The company\u2019s co-investor is Daylight Entertainment, and its legal representative is Hou Hongliang.<ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://tjcredit.gov.cn/platform/saic/viewBase.ftl?entId=1622f99353ee8a3c01766d18c709e197\n| title = \u5f97\u820d\u5f71\u89c6\uff08\u5929\u6d25\uff09\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8\n| date = February 25, 2016\n| accessdate =2017-11-10 |language=zh\n}}</ref>\n\n===Social===\nWang was part of [[Han Hong (singer)|Han Hong]]'s charity campaign to provide medical assistance in Gansu.<ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://ent.sina.com.cn/s/m/2016-06-03/doc-ifxsvenv6419018.shtml\n| title = \u97e9\u7ea2\"\u767e\u4eba\u63f4\u7518\"\u51fa\u53d1\u5728\u5373 \u59dc\u6587\u738b\u51ef\u52a0\u76df\n| date = June 3, 2016\n| accessdate =2017-11-10 |language=zh\n}}</ref> He was made ambassador of \"1219 Long Love\" public event in Beijing,<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u738b\u51ef\u83b7\u5c01\"\u767d\u624b\u6756\u5173\u7231\u5927\u4f7f\"_\u7f51\u6613\u5a31\u4e50|url = http://ent.163.com/photoview/00AJ0003/582176.html#p=BB9CB8FI00AJ0003|website =[[NetEase]]|accessdate = 2017-11-10}}</ref> [[Est\u00e9e Lauder Companies]]'s Greater China's Breast Cancer Awareness [[Pink ribbon]] program<ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://weibo.com/2831514415/E6QtnvRKB\n| title = \u738b\u51ef\u7c89\u7ea2\u4e1d\u5e26\u63a5\u529b\n| date = September 5, 2016\n| accessdate =2017-11-10|language=zh\n}}</ref> and appointed the Traffic Safety Ambassador for [[Beijing]].<ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://ent.sina.com.cn/s/m/2016-11-02/doc-ifxxmyuk5566105.shtml\n| title = \u738b\u51ef\u4e3a\u4ea4\u901a\u5b89\u5168\u4ee3\u8a00 \u547c\u5401\u4ece\u7cfb\u5b89\u5168\u5e26\u505a\u8d77\n| date = November 2, 2016\n| accessdate =2017-11-10|language=zh\n| work= [[Sina Corp|Sina]]\n}}</ref>\n\nAside from his own activities, Wang's fans  also made news in China for donating various roads in disadvantaged areas in the name of his characters,<ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/987162.shtml\n| title = Forget fanmail \u2013 young Chinese are finding a new way of paying tribute to their favorite stars: charity\n| date = June 6, 2016\n| work = [[The Global Times]] \n| accessdate = 2017-11-10\n}}</ref> including Ming Cheng, Xiao Jingyan, Fang Mengwei, Qi Yong, and Liu Chengzhi.<ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://weibo.com/1496916014/E45USqjf1\n| title = \u8c22\u8c22\u8fd9\u4e9b\u6709\u7231\u7684\u7c89\u4e1d\uff0c\u4eca\u5e74\u6350\u6b3e\u4fee\u4e865\u6761\u5c71\u8def\n| date = August 18, 2016\n| accessdate = 2017-11-10|language=zh\n}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!English title\n!Chinese title\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n|2012\n|''My Puppy My Love''  || \u6211\u7684\u72d7\u72d7\u6211\u7684\u7231\n|Shi Luwei \n| \n|-\n|2013\n|''A Young Girl's Destiny''  || \u9006\u88ad\n|Hao Chen\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/13/0909/10/98ATEDS8000300B1.html|title=\u300a\u9006\u88ad\u300b\u738b\u51ef\u6210\u540d\u53d8\u5927\u5496 \u4e0a\u6f14\u6bcd\u5b50\u50ac\u6cea\u6e29\u60c5|date=September 9, 2013|website=Netease|language=zh}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2014\n|''[[The Golden Era (film)|The Golden Era]]''  || \u9ec4\u91d1\u65f6\u4ee3\n|Jin Yi\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/m/c/2014-09-29/10244218216.shtml|title=\u300a\u9ec4\u91d1\u65f6\u4ee3\u300b\u9996\u6620 \u738b\u51ef\u5199\u5b9e\u98ce\u6f14\u7ece\u9773\u4ee5|date=September 29, 2014|website=Sina|language=zh}}</ref> \n|-\n|''[[A Murder Beside Yanhe River]]''  || \u9ec4\u514b\u529f\u6848\u4ef6\n|Huang Kegong\n| \n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Railroad Tigers]]''  || \u94c1\u9053\u98de\u864e\n|Fan Chuan\n| \n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"|2017\n|''[[The Devotion of Suspect X (film)|The Devotion of Suspect X]]''  || \u5acc\u7591\u4ebaX\u7684\u732e\u8eab\n|Tang Chuan\n| \n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"|2018\n|''[[A Better Tomorrow 2018]]''  || \u82f1\u96c4\u672c\u82722018\n|Zhou Kai \n| \n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"|2019\n| ''[[Dynasty Warriors (film)|Dynasty Warriors]]'' || \u771f\u4e09\u56fd\u65e0\u53cc\n| [[Cao Cao]] \n| \n|}\n\n=== Television series ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n!Year\n!English title\n!Chinese title\n!Role\n!Network \n!Notes\n|-\n|2006\n|''Cold Autumn''  || \u5bd2\u79cb\n|Huang Yuanshang\n| Chengdu Channel \n| \n|-\n|2008\n|''Water Point Peach Blossom''  || \u56f4\u5c4b\u91cc\u7684\u6843\u8